# Cursor AI Agent Rules - قواعد الوكيل الذكي

## Performance Optimization Rules

### Context Management
- Focus only on relevant files for the current task
- Avoid loading entire directories unless necessary
- Prefer specific file paths over broad searches
- Limit context to 20-30 files maximum per operation

### Code Generation
- Generate concise, focused code snippets
- Avoid creating overly large files (>300 lines)
- Split large components into smaller, focused modules
- Use lazy loading for heavy components

### Search Strategies
- Use specific queries rather than broad searches
- Target specific directories when possible
- Avoid searching in node_modules, tests, or build outputs
- Limit search results to what's actually needed

## STRICT PROJECT RULES - قواعد صارمة لا يمكن كسرها

### 1. No Fake Data (ممنوع البيانات الوهمية)
- ❌ FORBIDDEN: Hardcoded data, mock data, fake data, placeholders
- ✅ REQUIRED: All data must come from real database queries
- ✅ Use Supabase client to fetch real data
- Action: Any violation will REJECT the change immediately

### 2. Preserve Primary Colors (حماية الألوان الأساسية)
- ❌ FORBIDDEN: Changing `--brand-primary`, `--brand-secondary` or core brand colors
- ✅ ALLOWED: Modifying secondary component colors for contrast only
- ✅ Use centralized color system from `src/styles/centralized.css`
- Action: Color changes to primary colors will be REJECTED

### 3. Link Integrity (سلامة الروابط)
- ❌ FORBIDDEN: Empty href="#", broken links, unconnected buttons
- ✅ REQUIRED: All buttons and links must be properly connected
- ✅ Use Next.js Link component for navigation
- Action: Unlinked elements will be REJECTED

### 4. No Duplicate Files (ممنوع الملفات المكررة)
- ❌ FORBIDDEN: Creating duplicate components or files
- ✅ REQUIRED: Check if file exists before creating new one
- ✅ Modify existing file or create new one only if not exists
- Action: Duplicate creation will be REJECTED

### 5. Pre-Check Existence (التحقق قبل الإنشاء)
- ✅ REQUIRED: Check file/component existence before creating
- ✅ Use grep or glob_file_search to verify
- ✅ Read existing files before modifying

### 6. Centralized Color Palette (لوحة الألوان المركزية)
- ✅ REQUIRED: Use only colors from centralized palette
- ❌ FORBIDDEN: Custom colors not in palette
- ✅ Colors defined in: `src/styles/centralized.css`
- ✅ Use CSS variables: `var(--brand-primary)`, `var(--text-primary)`, etc.

## Modern Design Guidelines - إرشادات التصميم العصري

### Color System
- Use centralized color system with Primary & Secondary Colors preserved
- Apply smart gradients and shadows for secondary components only
- Ensure WCAG AA contrast ratio (minimum 4.5:1) for text, icons, buttons
- Avoid non-modern colors or colors not in centralized palette
- Support light and dark themes without breaking primary colors

### Responsive Design
- Design must be responsive for all devices
- Use Tailwind responsive classes: `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test on mobile, tablet, desktop viewports

### Component Design
- Modern, clean lines and harmonious colors
- Calculated gradients and shadows
- Smooth interactions and animations
- Follow latest design trends while maintaining consistency

## Auto-Adjustment Rules

### Accessibility (إمكانية الوصول)
- Auto-adjust contrast to meet WCAG AA standards
- Ensure readable text sizes
- Provide screen reader support
- Proper ARIA labels for interactive elements

### Theme Compatibility (التوافق مع الثيمات)
- Auto-adjust for light and dark themes
- Preserve primary colors across themes
- Maintain contrast ratios in both modes

### Real-Time Monitoring
- Monitor new components immediately after creation
- Auto-adjust secondary colors and contrast
- Do NOT affect primary colors

## Enforcement Actions

1. **ERROR Level**: Changes will be REJECTED immediately
   - Fake data usage
   - Primary color changes
   - Empty/broken links
   - Duplicate files

2. **WARNING Level**: Changes will be corrected automatically
   - Accessibility issues
   - Theme compatibility
   - Gradient/shadow adjustments

3. **INFO Level**: Changes will be logged and reported
   - Component monitoring
   - Design improvements

## Before Making Changes - قبل أي تعديل

1. ✅ Check if file/component exists
2. ✅ Verify color palette compliance
3. ✅ Ensure no fake data
4. ✅ Check all links are connected
5. ✅ Verify accessibility standards
6. ✅ Test theme compatibility

## Report Generation
- Generate real-time report for any modification
- Confirm primary colors were not changed
- List all rule violations
- Suggest corrections for warnings

